Package: multisiteDGP
Title: Data-Generating Processes for Multisite Trial Simulations
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R:
    person("JoonHo", "Lee", , "jlee296@ua.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0006-4019-8703"))
Description: Design defensible multisite trial simulations from
    summary-level building blocks. 'multisiteDGP' generates latent
    site effects under a catalog of eight distribution shapes (Gaussian,
    Student-t, skew-normal, asymmetric Laplace, two-component mixture,
    point-mass slab, user callback, and a Dirichlet-process-mixture
    bridge), calibrated sampling-error margins, intentional dependence
    between effects and precisions, and observed site estimates in a
    single call. Researchers express scenarios through intuitive
    quantities -- heterogeneity ratio, site counts, defensible presets
    -- rather than abstract variance components. Bundled diagnostics,
    presets calibrated to the JEBS, Walters, and Weiss literature, and
    adapters for 'metafor', 'baggr', and 'multisitepower' connect
    results to downstream analysis. Methods follow Lee, Che, Rabe-Hesketh,
    Feller, and Miratrix (2025) <doi:10.3102/10769986241254286>.
    Supported by IES through Grant R305D240078 to the University of
    Alabama.
